The paper deals with the analysis of probabilistic programs, which is a topic that falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of probabilistic pushdown automata (pPDA) also suggests a connection to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. The study of termination time and recurrence time in probabilistic programs also involves the use of statistical methods, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
